               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18491126-name-927" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18491126-name-927" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18491126-name-927" type="surname" value="LING"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18491126-name-927" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>JOSEPH LING</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the service of Mr. Alfred Ritchie, at Deptford. On 4th Nov., about half-past seven o'clock, I was watching my master's coal barges—I saw some boys taking the coals off the barges and putting them in a bag—I started after them between the barges—they ran to the other end—I</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184911260163"></xptr>
               <p>ran round and caught the prisoner, who had got thirty-three pounds of coals which belonged to Mr. Ritchie—the other boy got away.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I did not steal them; I have no father, and nobody to look after me but my mother; she is a widow and has six children; I am the eldest.</p>
